By JONATHAN SWAN and MAGGIE HABERMAN

President Biden and Donald J. Trump have agreed to two debates, one on June 7 at the CNN office on Sept. 10 at ABC News, the first onstage debate between the former president and his successor in more than three years.

While some of the detail were still being hammered out, the agreement in the two debates, reached in a series of social-media posts Thursday morning, raises the likelihood of the earliest possible debate in the months to come.
